The paper discusses a method for robotic in-hand manipulation, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach is bio-mimetic, which involves modeling human behavior, and can be considered as an application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The method uses tactile sensors to predict local slip, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV). The paper proposes a modular approach, which can be considered as a machine learning technique (cs.LG). Finally, the method involves control of multi-digit robotic hands, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
